    # [Scene: Rehabilitated Quay | Morning]

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Warm, steady strings; light percussion like heartbeat]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Seagulls, distant hammering, quiet chatter; water lapping against pilings]
    "You wake to the smell of salt and citrus — Elena's package still warm in your bag like an echo of the night you all chose to plant instead of abandoning. The heavy rain that hammered"
    "the town edged away overnight; the sky is pale and clean, as if the world has exhaled. Around you, the quay is not the same quay it was a week ago. It is stitched: a hybrid"
    "seam of engineer-cut blocks and the ragged green of new mangrove shoots, tied together by rope, community hands, and something else that feels like faith."
    show elena_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    elena_navarro "Look at this, niña. You did that."
    "She says it without grand words — just the blunt warmth of pride — and you feel the statement settle in your chest. It is not only yours. It never was. But you carried the plan"
    "through the hardest hours. You carried people's trust when they were tired of being asked for it."
    show mayor_isla_cortez at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_isla_cortez "Aria, Kavir—this looks... accountable. Practical. And the proposal in writing is sound."
    show dr_kavir_singh at center:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_kavir_singh "The data align with the pilot results. The modules reduce peak surge by the modeled margin, and the mangrove buffer shows measurable attenuation at the outer line."
    "Kavir's voice is the steady thing that translates the tautness in the room into numbers everyone can hold. His approval moves the mayor. You have always known that science is a way of making promises visible."

    mayor_isla_cortez "But the council will insist on oversight. They asked about funding strings—outside agencies trying to tie us to control in exchange for resources. We need to be clear what we accept."
    "You let your fingers trail in the brine-dark water, feeling the small pull of tide under the pier. You remember the grant proposal that arrived like a polished hand — funds enough to scale quickly, but"
    "with clauses that would hand over procurement and decision-making to a distant board. The money could expedite modules and sensors. It could also unmoor the town's voice."
    hide elena_navarro
    show aria_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "We can build faster with their money. We can test more systems. But we lose the right to decide what 'resilience' means here."
    hide mayor_isla_cortez
    show mateo_hale at right:
        zoom 0.7

    mateo_hale "And what does 'resilience' mean to you, Aria? Not hypotheticals—what do you want this place to be?"
    "Mateo's question lands with a steady, warm precision. He has always measured with his hands, with plans and drafts, but this time he is asking for what the town means, not what the calculations say."

    menu:
        "Bring up the stewardship council bylaws now":
            "You pull out your notebook and outline the governance structure you've been drafting—terms, rotating seats, veto safeguards. The group leans in, marks pages, murmurs approval."
        "Invite everyone to a ceremonial planting instead":
            "You suggest sealing the agreement with action: a planting where signatures are next to hands in mud. Faces brighten—people like the symbolism. Elena claps her hands like a child at a party."

    # --- merge ---
    "Both routes draw the room together. You watch Mateo and Kavir exchange a look over the notebook—Kavir's eyebrows lift, Mateo's mouth tightens in a way you recognize as him preparing to commit. Mayor Isla studies Katie the municipal ledger in her head, and then nods."
    hide dr_kavir_singh
    show mayor_isla_cortez at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_isla_cortez "If the council is local, elected, and has a binding seat at procurement decisions, the municipality will step back from accepting outside strings. We'll allocate emergency funds in the short term, and if you all accept public auditing, I will sign it into policy."
    hide aria_navarro
    show dr_kavir_singh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_kavir_singh "And we'll publish the methodologies openly—replicable, community-run maintenance protocols. No handcuffs, just scaffolding."
    "You feel the old, familiar guilt at the edge of your vision—the part of you that believes sacrifice is the only moral currency. But it is softer now, tempered by the sight of neighbors with soil"
    "under their nails and the way Mateo's hand finds yours on the railing and doesn't let go."
    hide mateo_hale
    show aria_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "No strings. We'll decline the grant. We'll build the council, the bylaws, and the public auditing. We take responsibility—and we accept help on terms we define."
    hide mayor_isla_cortez
    show elena_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    elena_navarro "Good. You've got backbone, niña. And you've got company."
    "Declining the outside money feels like a physical motion — an unhooking. It costs time and risk. It gives the town back its agency. You turn the decision over in your mouth like a citrus peel; bitter, bright, grounding."
    hide dr_kavir_singh
    show mateo_hale at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mateo_hale "You did that. You chose it."

    aria_navarro "I didn't do it alone."
    # [Scene: Rooftop Greenhouse & Community Rooftop | Late Afternoon]
    hide aria_navarro
    hide elena_navarro
    hide mateo_hale

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_2 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, intimate guitar; a gentle swell of wind chimes]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The muted hum of the town below, a faraway child's laugh]
    "Later, you climb the familiar crooked ladder to the greenhouse where you and Mateo have stolen quiet hours before. The plants smell like wet soil and lemon basil. Up here, the town is a small, breathing"
    "thing; down there, decisions echo into lives. Here, the echo is only for you and him."
    show mateo_hale at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mateo_hale "You look like someone who just refused a golden handcuff."
    show aria_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "I do not accept handcuffs. Not when people hand me keys instead."

    mateo_hale "Then let's make sure we always keep the keys where people can reach them. And—' (he searches your face) '—and if you ever want to hand one of those to me, I won't try to lock it away."
    "There's a pause that fills with things once unspoken: the nights of shared maps and the way he tightened bolts when your hands trembled; the small texts at 2 a.m. with sketches that had his awkward"
    "heart scribbled in the margins. You have feared choosing love the way you'd feared a leak: one sudden surrender all at once. But standing here, in the warm hush, it feels less like drowning and more"
    "like walking into a home you help build together."

    menu:
        "Take his hand":
            "Your fingers curl around his, tentative at first, then with ease. He lets out a breath you don't hear but feel in his shoulders. You both laugh, like a secret shared."
        "Lean in and rest your head on his shoulder":
            "You lean, and the greenhouse smells of basil and sun. He slips his arm around you, protective and gentle; you stay there, anchored, as if the world could rearrange but this could hold."

    # --- merge ---
    "There's a pause that fills with things once unspoken: the nights of shared maps and the way he tightened bolts when your hands trembled; the small texts at 2 a.m. with sketches that had his awkward heart scribbled in the margins."

    mateo_hale "I don't have all the answers. But I have a steady hand and a stubborn belief that something can be both useful and whole. Will you—' (he stops, then finishes) '—will you let me be part of choosing how we keep this place? Not as a fix, but as a partner?"

    aria_navarro "Yes. We build together. We argue, we forgive, and we choose the long, messy way—together."

    mateo_hale "Good. Then let's promise—no unilateral fixes. We argue in the sun, not the storm."

    aria_navarro "And if you ever sulk in hard hats, I will let you. But only for an hour."
    "You make the promise with a small, private ceremony of two. He takes your hand and the world narrows to the sound of your breath and the soft rustle of leaves. Hope, for once, is not a mere projection—it is a plan with a person attached to it."
    # [Scene: The Tidal Lab | Evening — First Major Test]
    hide mateo_hale
    hide aria_navarro

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Triumphant but understated strings; a chorus of shared breath]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The wind rising, soft applause from the quay, the distant call of a bell signaling a successful test]
    "Weeks pass. You fine-tune the modules with Jun's cunning tweaks; the mangroves thicken their ranks. The stewardship council convenes, rotating seats occupied by fishers, engineers, elders, and youth. The bylaws are inked in a ceremonial planting—signatures"
    "beside mud and small, stubborn roots. At the lab, you watch the first scheduled surge test: a modeled storm that would, last year, have taken half the quay."
    show dr_kavir_singh at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_kavir_singh "Model predicts a thirty percent reduction in wave energy where both barriers exist. Real-time data coming in now."
    "Then the sea comes—a grey wall not of rage but of weight. The modules flex, joints shifting like vertebrae. The outer mangrove line takes the first of the chop, and you can almost see the water's"
    "rhythm slow as roots and engineered mass negotiate space. Sensors sing: numbers steady, thresholds met. People on the quay hold their breath and then release it in one long, collective exhale."
    show sora_lin at right:
        zoom 0.7

    sora_lin "You made it work."
    show aria_navarro at center:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "We made it—together."

    sora_lin "I wanted to bulldoze the whole engineering plan. You gave me a seat at the table instead. I was angry before; I'm less angry now."
    "Sora's face is an unreadable map—relief folded into reservation. They hug you in a no-nonsense, half-playful way that says more than any official apology. It is the kind of reconciliation that does not erase differences but rearranges them into a new structure."
    hide dr_kavir_singh
    show mayor_isla_cortez at left:
        zoom 0.7

    mayor_isla_cortez "This council will be the model for our funding streams. No outside board will have veto without our consent. The municipality will provide seed funds, if the council ensures transparency and community-led maintenance."
    hide sora_lin
    show elena_navarro at right:
        zoom 0.7

    elena_navarro "Look at you—all of you. You're keeping the town's heart in its chest."
    "You stand at the lab's open door with Mateo at your side. The phone lights you used to carry like talismans are now simple tools; the diver's watch on your wrist ticks with a certain gentleness."
    "Around you, the town hums—repair crews trading jokes with volunteers, Jun fiddling with a sensor until it sings exactly right, kids chasing each other between saplings. The hybrid model isn't some pristine compromise on paper: it"
    "is a living thing. It creaks and adapts and takes some losses and some wins, but it holds."
    hide aria_navarro
    show mateo_hale at center:
        zoom 0.7

    mateo_hale "We did the work. You asked us to stay in the hard places without giving away the map. We did that."
    hide mayor_isla_cortez
    show aria_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "We asked. They answered. We keep answering."
    "Hope is not absence of fear here; it is the presence of enough hands and plans to meet fear when it comes. The council meets, disputes, sleeps, argues again. The town votes on procurement with open"
    "minutes and public workshops. The stewards check the sensors and teach children to read tide lines the way their grandparents did."

    menu:
        "Join the council meeting to present long-term maintenance plans":
            "You stand before the council and lay out a decade of community-led maintenance: seed swaps, workshop rotations, apprenticeship paths. Faces nod; someone jokes about your obsession with spreadsheets. It lands."
        "Walk the shoreline at dusk with Mateo and just listen":
            "You walk the reclaimed edge, Mateo's arm around your shoulders. You don't speak much. You listen to the water and each other. That quiet is its own agreement."

    # --- merge ---
    "At dusk, the quay is alive with low laughter and the smell of frying fish — Elena's trade, now a celebration. String lights bob like stars reclaimed from the tide. You let the warmth of that"
    "moment soak into the places in you that had hardened into duty. Mateo pulls you close; Sora is painting a mural that will mark the new boundary; Jun runs up with a sensor reading that makes"
    "Kavir whoop."
    hide elena_navarro
    show dr_kavir_singh at right:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_kavir_singh "You made the right call, Aria. Science without stewardship is a little god. Stewardship without science becomes superstition. You've bent both toward the common good."

    aria_navarro "We bent and sometimes snapped. But we mended, too."
    "The hybrid holds in the first real test. It will not be the last test — storms will come, tides will rise and recede, the human work of tending and adjusting will continue. But you feel"
    "the current under the town has shifted: not drained, not saved, but guided. The town is learning to be both builder and gardener."

    mateo_hale "Do you ever think about leaving? About the grant, the labs abroad—"

    aria_navarro "I thought about it. I still get the letters. But staying feels like choosing a life that is smaller in means but larger in meaning. And—' (you touch his face) '—and it's a life I want to share."
    "He smiles like someone finally allowed to fold his plans into someone else's map. The night gathers around you without closing in. Above, the stars are smeared by city glow, but the rooftop greenhouse lights make constellations of their own."
    hide mateo_hale
    hide aria_navarro
    hide dr_kavir_singh

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_4 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Full, warm strings; a chorus of voices in harmony]
    "Years may bring new pressures, new storms, new choices. But tonight you stand where hope and work meet, anchored by community, by partnership, by the stubborn, patient life of mangroves and the exacting geometry of Mateo's drawings. You are no longer the only one carrying the map."
    show aria_navarro at left:
        zoom 0.7

    aria_navarro "We built a model that belongs to us. We chose each other and this town."
    "As you let the sentence settle, the quay fills with a soft, approving murmur. Elena presses another wrapped bundle into your hands — citrus and fried fish again, and you laugh. You feel light and heavy at once: responsible, yes, but not burdened alone."
    hide aria_navarro

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Gentle resolution; a single piano motif repeats with calm finality]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The sea, patient and steady]

    scene bg ch6_4001e7_6 at full_bg
    "THE END"
